Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Фреш Арисара Вонгчали","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"阿裏薩拉·旺查裏","primary":false}}]}},"person_55755_translations":{"at":1772469946741,"data":{"id":55755,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Richard Timothy Jones is an American actor. He has worked extensively in both film and television productions since the early 1990s. His television roles include Ally McBeal (1997), Judging Amy (1998–2005), CSI: Miami (2006), Girlfriends (2007), Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles (2008-2009), Grey's Anatomy (2010), Hawaii Five-0 (2011–2014), Narcos (2015), and Criminal Minds (2017). Since 2018, he has played Police Sergeant Wade Grey on the ABC police drama The Rookie.\n\nHis film roles include portrayals of Lamont Carr in Disney's Full Court Miracle (2003), Laveinio \"Slim\" Hightower in Rick Famuyiwa's coming-of-age film The Wood (1999), Mike in Tyler Perry's dramatic films Why Did I Get Married? (2007) and Why Did I Get Married Too? (2010), and Captain Russell Hampton in the Hollywood blockbuster Godzilla (2014).","name":"Richard T. Jones","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"ES","iso_639_1":"es","name":"Español","english_name":"Spanish","data":{"biography":"Richard Timothy Jones (altura 1,88 m) nacido el 16 de enero de 1972) es un actor de cine y televisión estadounidense. Jones nació en Kobe, Japón y se crió en Carson, California. Él es el hijo de Lorene. analista informático, y Clarence Jones, jugador profesional de béisbol e instructor de bateo de los Indios de Cleveland. También tiene un hermano mayor llamado Clarence Jones Jr., que ahora trabaja como entrenador. Sus padres se divorciaron más tarde. Jones se graduó de Bishop Montgomery High Escuela en Torrance, California.","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_nam